name: Swayle
businessDescription:
Swayle is all about making sales smarter and more personalized. We’ve created a tool that helps sales teams connect with their prospects in a way that feels natural and human, but without all the time-consuming manual work. Our platform uses AI to gather detailed information about each prospect and then helps craft personalized outreach that really resonates. The best part? It all integrates seamlessly with HubSpot, so salespeople can keep using the tools they’re already familiar with.

In a nutshell, Swayle takes the guesswork out of sales outreach, making it easier for teams to engage with the right people at the right time, and ultimately close more deals. We’re focused on helping businesses improve their sales process by combining the power of AI with the personal touch that’s so crucial in building relationships.
longBusinessDescription:
Many sales teams struggle with the same issue: they spend too much time on repetitive tasks like gathering information about prospects and personalizing their outreach. This process is not only time-consuming but also inefficient. Salespeople often end up sending generic emails because they just don’t have the bandwidth to personalize every message properly. This means they miss out on opportunities to really connect with potential customers.
This is a big problem because, in today’s world, people expect personalized communication. If a prospect feels like they’re just another name on a list, they’re less likely to respond or engage. This lack of personalization leads to lower response rates, fewer meaningful conversations, and ultimately, fewer deals closed. For sales teams, that means a lot of wasted time and effort with little to show for it.
Solving this problem would mean that sales teams can reach out to prospects in a way that feels relevant and thoughtful. It would make their communication more effective, leading to higher response rates, better relationships with prospects, and more closed deals. In short, it would make their sales process much more efficient and successful.
Swayle solves this problem by using AI to take care of the heavy lifting. Our platform automatically gathers detailed information about each prospect, like their role, company, and recent activities. It then uses this information to help sales teams craft personalized messages that really speak to the prospect’s needs and interests. And because Swayle is fully integrated with HubSpot, all of this happens right within the tools that salespeople are already using, making it easy and seamless. This means sales teams can spend less time on repetitive tasks and more time building relationships and closing deals.

name: Infinigrid
businessDescription: Real-time analysis and risk forecasting to optimize grid operations using SaaS.
longBusinessDescription:
Promaps provides you with holistic, real-time insights essential for efficiently operating your grid and preparing it for the ongoing energy transition. Our probabilistic risk management solution helps identify and mitigate risks within your system, allowing you to capitalize on future opportunities more swiftly.
Leveraging big data and a digital twin of your power system, in concert with proprietary mathematic modeling, we calculate the anticipated energy that will not be delivered. Our proprietary software employs Markov models to continuously enhance your risk management capabilities and harness technological advancements.
Our goal is to be your trusted partner in managing all aspects of your grid operations.
Software features encompass:
Data APIs can connect Promaps technology to operations systems / digital twin platform, and third-party data like weather data
Real-time probabilistic risk calculations of your power system
Failure probability for each component, branch and system
Risk for loss of load in MWh/h for each load and the whole system
Web-based operational dashboard for intuitive live reports and overall system status
Model scenarios and test risk mitigation actions and strategies on a digital twin of your power system
tags: Real-time insights to seucurity of power supply

At NordicHQ, we've built our service around this principle.
You can spend countless hours studying market reports, tax regulations, and business etiquettes. You can learn the rules, systems, and common practices, but there is often more to it. As much as it is about what you know, it is about who you know. NordicHQ takes care of just that: connecting you to a network of knowledgeable, responsive, and entrepreneurial professionals in Northern Europe.
Our model is designed to offer a wide array of services, from legal advice to market entry strategies, through our robust partner network. This network is composed of local experts who not only provide you with relevant insights but also link you to potential clients, partners, and investors in the region.
In the fast-paced world of entrepreneurship, time is often of the essence. NordicHQ ensures swift communication with our clients through advanced technology platforms and dedicated customer service, so you can make well-informed decisions promptly.
Whether you are a fledgling startup or an established enterprise looking to venture into the Northern European market, NordicHQ is your reliable partner for scalable growth and success.

name: SmartEmploy
businessDescription: Our goal is to establish a portal for a simpler and better connection between apprenticeships(businesses) and apprentices, based on compliance between the company's requirements and the apprentice's interests and prerequisites.
longBusinessDescription:
Background for the project
Our goal is to establish a portal for a simpler and better connection between apprenticeships(businesses) and apprentices, based on compliance between the company's requirements and the apprentice's interests and prerequisites. Structured mapping and tests will help the apprentices to find out which apprenticeship companies are most relevant, and in parallel contribute to the apprenticeship companies finding apprentices with good prerequisites for success - also among those with a low-grade level and/or a lot of absenteeism.
Grade versus grades - an alternative approach to assessing suitability as an apprentice
Psychometric testing
This is today an established and recognized method in recruitment processes. Used in a matching platform, it lays the foundation for a simpler selection from the learning companies, by giving them access to student profiles that are ranked according to the company's needs.
Who are we?
We are a training office registered in Bærum municipality in Viken.
What are we doing?
Our goal is to develop and operate an apprenticeship portal that helps apprentices in all vocational subjects throughout Norway find the best possible apprenticeship. Recruiting companies and public enterprises to the apprenticeship scheme is an important contribution to achieving the goal. Through greater knowledge of the scheme, help to be approved as an apprenticeship company, and a good matching system in one and the same portal, it should be possible to increase the number from the current 20,000 active apprenticeship companies.
By using psychometric testing, the apprentice will, instead of being assessed largely on grades and absenteeism percentage, be able to present a holistic picture of himself that the company will find interesting.

name: Shepherd
businessDescription: Shepherd is a productivity tool integrating with the calendar and video conferencing to help teams reduce friction and improve meeting efficiency, while also providing a way to instantly synchronise all meeting information with other work tools (Slack, Trello, Notion, CRMs, etc.).
longBusinessDescription:
In a nutshell, Shepherd is a meeting productivity tool helping companies set and run structured and productive meetings, without any friction. We then make it intuitive for our user/s to connect all the information from the meeting (e.g. tasks, agendas, notes, documents) to other commonly used tools (e.g. Notion, Trello, CRMs, Slack etc.).
How it works:
a.) Shepherd integrates directly with the work calendar making it simple for the users to navigate between meeting events. Right now the calendar serves as the meeting navigation dashboard, however we're in the process of building out an all-in-one dashboard to give the user the option to navigate from a searchable list of meetings too.
b) The user can create a custom agenda template for each meeting type (e.g. Daily Standup) which can be imported into any meeting within 2 clicks.
c) Shepherd then integrates directly into your video conferencing. This allows the user to read off the pre-set agenda, take collaborative and shared meeting notes, and create new tasks, without navigating away fro the video screen.
d) Then once the meeting is completed, the user can integrate Shepherd with an array of other tools such as Slack, Notion, Trello, to name a few. The user can export note, outcomes, summaries and action items to where they need to be. If the user does not use any other tools, they can lean on Shepherd to provide a home for all of their meeting information.
We're also working on building a range of other features/functionalities such as:
- A visual timer for the agenda
- Microlearning nudges to coach users how to effectively run or attend a meeting (e.g. if a 60-minute meeting does not have an agenda 2 days before the meeting, Shepherd will prompt the meeting lead to create an agenda)
- Tag/sort/categorize meetings so that can easily be accessed at any time
- Meeting transcription to make note-taking simple and hands-free
- AI meeting assistant
- Asynchronous video recordings (with timestamps)
- Other 3rd party integrations
- Analytics and insights (which can be fed back to the user)
- Plus many many more
Essentially, we've created a conduit between the calendar/video and other well-known work tools used by teams. We are complementing existing tools, rather than trying to force a change in workflows and behavior.
Our aim is for Shepherd to be a core part of every team's productivity stack. Shepherd can also be used in distributed and in-person meetings, the only difference being the need for video conferencing.
tags: Productivity, Collaboration, SaaS, Future of Work

name: Drowzee
businessDescription: Drowzee’s product, Pendulum, is offered as an at-home solution for people with sleep complaints while being easy to use, globally accessible, reduces the operational cost of treatment, and turns sleep insights into gamified executable actions. Pendulum helps people improve their sleep through a combination of brain training, sleep monitoring, and data analytics.The product improves time to fall asleep, while reducing awakenings during the night.
longBusinessDescription:
Pendulum is plug and play, based on science, and makes improving sleep engaging by augmenting data insights into pragmatic actions. The science behind it is inspired by a heritage of research, called operant conditioning, and further developed in-house, based on real user data and analytics.
The solution consists of a EEG headset, capable of reading brain activity in real-time, and a mobile application for keeping an overview of data analytics and suggestions for action. It allows the user to conduct brain training, which rebalances the brain for better sleep, monitor and track their sleep quality, and receive concrete suggestions for improvements.
The headband itself can be worn during the night for tracking and analysing sleep. However, the Pendulum also allows for third party sleep monitor integration for more accurate data gathering. Data from the headband and integrated devices are utilised to provide the users with pragmatic suggestions for how to improve their sleep health.
Our ambition is to provide the best solution of connected bedroom devices so that users can get an ultimate experience in terms of brain training, meta-insights and gamified executable tasks for improving their sleep health.
The scientific concept behind the brain training is a technique known as neurofeedback training (NFT). NFT allows users to:
 (1) Gain insight into the brain processes which are the root cause of their neuropathology and
(2) To rebalance the dysregulated brain patterns which underlie their symptoms.
Neurofeedback is currently available to insomniacs, as well as people suffering from other neuropathologies, in neurofeedback clinics.
Drowzee has developed a unique approach to provide remote neurofeedback training for sleep improvement, with a view to reduce mental distress and enhance sleep quality. Unlike competitors, Drowzee provides a solution that goes far beyond other sleep monitoring, as it combines it with advanced brain training.

We reduce anxiety associated with borrowing and minimize risks associated with lending, while at the same time strategically turning past borrowers into future investors. By using IoT sensors to analyze the human-made noise, Waved automatically adjusts the music volume to a perfect level - no matter the circumstances. We make the restaurant and hospitality experience better, no more shouting to hold a conversation - the background music is always well balanced.
longBusinessDescription:
WHY WAVED?
THE CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE
The goal of restaurants, bars and other eating and drinking venues is to provide the best customer experience possible. The customer’s well-being is directly linked to the amount of money spent during their stay and the likelihood that they will return.
THE IMPORTANCE OF SOUND
Research has shown that a well composed sound environment has direct impact on how the guest’s overall experience and even how the taste of the food and drinks are perceived.
LARGE INVESTMENTS IN SOUND EQUIPMENT
Most restaurants and bars know how important the sound environment is for a good customer experience and it is common to spend thousands of dollars on sound equipment.
WHAT DECIDES THE VOLUME?
The volume is usually controlled manually by waiters or bartenders in-between their other duties. Lack of information and knowledge of the customers perception often lead to poor volume level decisions.
THE SOLUTION IS WAVED
Wall-mounted sensors are placed around the venue and listens to the sound environment. Waved’s brain is build around our self-developed algorithm. It has the ability to understand and evaluate the sound environment and is used to set the perfect sound volume in order to maximise the customer experience.

name: qbee AS
businessDescription: Embedded Linux device management and remote access - SaaS
longBusinessDescription:
Embedded Linux device management and remote access with integrated VPN.  
Industry 4.0, Smart City, Smart Building and many other IoT applications have a common challenge. They involve a lot of different edge devices that all need to be managed throughout their lifecycle. On a typical shop floor or in a smart city deployment there are dozens of different devices that all need to have security settings in place, that need to be updated and configured as well as maintained until decommissioning.  https://qbee.io solves all this by providing a flexible agent that can be installed on any Linux device without the need for additional development work. It is lightweight and pull-based which allows the units to connect from basically any company network or firewall as well as through mobile networks. The build in VPN makes it possible to securely access the remote devices out of the box either through remote ssh access or through full web server access with the qbee-connect desktop tool. Utilizing a VNC client like RealVNC or similar qbee turns quickly into an embedded Teamviewer alternative allowing to simply check what is happening on a remote device. Integrated performance metric monitoring allows to quickly discover any deviations within the device fleet. This can identify log file creeping, flash issues or just high load.  qbee.io provides a full analysis of all software libraries used and checks against the NIST CVE security database. This allows to proactively identify security issues such as heartbleed or similar.  One major functionality of qbee is the configuration management. This part allows OTA software updates of libraries and packages. Together with file distribution and templating this allows to easily configure any application or Linux service. In contrast to Chef, Puppet, SaltStack or Ansible qbee is pull-based. This allows to configure devices based on state rather than to tell the edge units what to do. All devices (also spare devices that might have been offline for years) will receive the latest configuration and converge to that. All this with a minimum footprint and impact on other device functionality. This is very useful to keep ssh keys concurrent for all devices even while rotating them on a regular basis. Typical customers of qbee are system operators that need to maintain a diverse fleet of edge devices, both new and legacy ones. Here a single pane of view helps to get a full overview quickly. Manufacturers of machinery and industrial solutions can use qbee as a remote device management tool without the need for investing into their own development. This allows for fast POCs (proof of concept) as well as for very good ROI (return on investment). Embedded board device manufacturers can offer qbee as a pre-installed solution enabling their customers to achieve a quick time to value. 
 We are happy to get in touch with you and let you know more about our solution. We also offer a 30 day free trial: https://qbee.io/trial/
tags: IoT, device management, embedded Linux, operational technology

name: Sensibel
businessDescription:
sensiBel’s patented optical ultra-low noise MEMS (Micro-Electro-Mechanical System) microphone features >80dB Signal-to-Noise-Ratio (SNR), without compromising Acoustic Overload Point (AOP) and Total Harmonic Distortion (THD) - a quantum leap in performance compared to today's mainstream MEMS microphones. 
The improvement of the key microphone parameter (SNR) for MEMS microphones has reached a ceiling with today’s transducer technologies. Small improvements in performance can be achieved by e.g. including additional transducers elements in a MEMS package. This approach quickly adds complexity and cost, and can only go so far. A new transducer technology is required to make a significant leap in performance – optical MEMS!

sensiBel’s patented optical MEMS technology that makes the microphone so sensitive is based on a combination of two optical phenomena; interference and diffraction, both of which are due to the wave character of light. In simple terms, the microphone uses a tiny energy-efficient laser to measure extremely accurately the motion of a silicon-based membrane, thanks to the integrated photodetector readout system. This ultra-low self-noise readout principle gives the high SNR characteristic, yet in a small MEMS package with low power consumption.

Additional benefits of the optical MEMS transducer system are enhanced environmental robustness e.g. against dust, and significantly reduced likelihood for stiction (the membrane stuck to the backplate).

SonoClear reduces image artifacts by mimicking the physical properties of brain tissue.

longBusinessDescription:
The oil, gas and shipping industry is fickle. 
There are ups and downs, and any industry player looking to maintain and sustain business needs to adapt quickly.  For the oil, gas and shipping supply industry that means it’s common sense to stock up on equipment, spares and inventory when fair winds blow, and quickly sell when it turns. 
Staying on top of market fluctuations is not always easy. As a result, production intensive products tend to stockpile, surplus equipment gathers dust, and even high volume materials have a hard time finding target buyers. At the same time potential buyers are spending valuable resources sourcing the market.
That’s where SurplusHub® come in. 
SurplusHub is the culmination of 30+ years of industry experience, lessons learned from hard bouts in the supply chain and a deep analysis of market needs.
We offer a global online trading platform for surplus equipment and materials that’s safe, transparent, environmentally and financially friendly, offers an interface designed from the ground up to be user friendly, and every transaction can be backed by high quality third-party services.
Open 24/7, all over the world.

businessDescription:

The company focuses on the total utilization of seaweeds for the production of unique, pure, and formulated products in a multifunctional biorefinery. Through safe, eco-friendly, and efficient operations, Alginor sets the standard for tomorrow’s innovative solutions and technologies.
Alginor ASA was established on 24th March 2014 to commercialize know-how and technology through the construction of an integrated Biorefinery for seaweeds.

Seaweeds are among the world’s largest untapped resource. Norway’s seaweed forest constitutes 80 % of the coastal biomass with a standing stock estimated to 50 million tons. However, in order to utilize seaweeds effectively, it is necessary to use a technology that exploits the entire biomass – a biorefinery.

Alginor plans to start up the first biorefinery in Norway focusing on total (i.e. 100 %) utilization and resource-efficient processing of seaweeds to pure and formula-specific products for use in food, feed, pharma, agri, chemicals, and materials. The biorefinery will be in the form of a Demonstration unit with a tentative production capacity of 5,000 tons of seaweed per year. Further, Alginor plans a new expansion to a full-scale industrial Biorefinery with an annual production capacity of 50,000 tons of seaweed per year.
